creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Birds and All Nature, Vol. V, No 2 February 1899 by Various.
Read in English by Diana Schmidt; Nanette Notestein; Kathrine Engan; Eliza Winters; Scott Bennett; Nathan Stone; Vern Seward; Availle; Kimberlie Sasan; Martin Campbell; Geza Hrazdina
"Birds and All Nature" was a monthly publication of the Nature Study Publishing Company of Chicago. It includes short poems and brief descriptions of birds, animals and other natural subjects with accompanying color plates. The magazine was published from 1897-1907 under the various titles, "Birds," "Birds and all Nature," "Nature and Art" and "Birds and Nature." - Summary by J. M. Smallheer

"England holds the honor of having first formed societies for the prevention of cruelty to animals and of having first legislated for its punishment." -anon


For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
